  "body": "- [x] I've [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nWe have a large truffle test suite in JS that was passing entirely on truffle v 5.1.23. We needed to upgrade it to get a new package that requires truffle v >= 5.1.35. We encountered several weird errors so decided to upgrade to latest truffle, which is 5.4.11. With this I am seeing some odd behavior where tests that previously were passing are now failing with \"out of gas\" errors.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the \"out of gas\" errors, logs are showing several `Ambiguous event, possible interpretations` errors, which don't really make any sense.\r\n\r\nPerhaps truffle's default transaction gas limit changed to a lower value somewhere in between these two versions, but there is no documentation about this. I also can't find any way to override this value globally, as opposed to setting a `gas` field on every single transaction.\r\n\r\n2 issues: 1) how to set global gas limit on every truffle tx? 2) why does truffle show \"Ambiguous event, possible interpretations\" errors when the real error is out-of-gas?\r\n\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Linux\r\n* Ethereum client: (?) solc version 0.5.17\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.11\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 14.17.3\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.14.13\r\n",
