    "body": "OK, so, there are several different things going on here.  I think this should be multiple issues.\r\n\r\nSo, what changed regarding gas?  (Thanks to @fainashalts for this explanation.)  Prior to 5.4.11, the default gas limit was the block limit, which was a gross overestimation for most use cases. Now a call to the `estimateGas()` function is made to estimate the gas needed for a transaction. This is then multiplied by 1.5 for the gas limit. If 1.5 x gas is higher than the blockLimit for the latest block, the blockLimit is used instead.\r\n\r\nThis change *shouldn't* have broken anything, but apparently it did.  So that's one issue.  Why did it break things?  I don't know; but if you have a reproduction example, we'd be glad to inspect it and see what's going on.\r\n\r\nSecondly, we have the question of how to set `gas` globally for tests.  Well, you can set `gas` globally for a network with the `gas` setting for that network in your Truffle config.  However, if you're running Truffle Test where you're not running it against an existing network (such as a separately-running instance of Ganache), um, I'm not sure we support setting global config options in that case.  So that's a second issue (but also a workaround -- use a separately-running instance of Ganache and put it in your Truffle Config -- or possibly a solution for your use case if you were already using a separately-running instance of Ganache).\r\n\r\nAs for the event thing: I have no idea.  That's a third issue.  However, if you have a reproduction example, I can check it out and see what's up with that.\r\n\r\nSo, would you mind renaming this and splitting it up?  Thanks!  (We can add the second issue if you don't, since we don't really need reproduction information for that one.  But we're going to need repro information to proceed with the first and third.)",
