    "body": "Again, you seem to be combining together what is potentially a number of different issues.  If we are to address these problems, we need to first break it down into discrete problems, and have clear reproduction steps for each.  If you change things, and you get different problems as a result, then those new problems are different issues, not the same issue; if you are seeing new problems that you did not see before, then you should file new issues, not comment on them here.\r\n\r\nI would really suggest that you should split this up into multiple issues, with explicit reproduction steps for each and records of the resulting problems, if we are to make progress on solving it.  Trying to reproduce and investigate some of these multiple problems, based solely on the information provided here, seems like it could potentially be quite difficult.  Like, when you discuss non-determinism, what non-determinism exactly are you seeing?  What precisely differs between runs that should be identical?  (Again, though, you should file a new issue for this, not answer here.)\r\n\r\nSince you have linked your test suite, though, we can use that as a starting point for investigation.  So that's helpful; thanks for that.  I'll try it out and see what I can find regarding the problems you initially reported, i.e., an out of gas that shouldn't happen (on the one hand) and this ambiguous event message (on the other hand).  Maybe the nondeterminism will even turn up, who knows!",
