    "body": "Hi @SidSethi I just want to speak to the gas issues you are facing, it sounds like there are a couple of other things going on here but hopefully I can help. \r\n\r\n-- can you update your node version? We only support versions 10 and up (perhaps this was a typo? We don't think Truffle would run at all on Node 4!)\r\n-- you cannot set `gasPrice` at the configuration level at this time. You will need to add it in each transaction, like `{ gasPrice: ____ }`\r\n-- you can set `gas` at the configuration level, which I see you have done. However, the gas * 1.5 (our default gas multiplier) should be less than the latest `blockLimit` (`gas` is the most gas you are willing to spend, `blockLimit` is the most gas that can be spent in the block). \r\n-- I suggest you add gasMultiplier to your contracts and set it to 1 (i.e. `Registry.gasMultiplier = 1`) before deployment steps happen.  \r\n\r\nI see you have a `development` network specified in your config. I am assuming that this is what you are using in your tests, as Truffle will try to use that by default if it is specified.\r\n\r\nThe event issues should be in another issue so we can properly track them. Can you please write up a separate issue for that so we can dig in? Thanks!",
