    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So I was able to get some cases of \"ambiguous events\" messages where this didn't seem to make sense.  However, I should note that this didn't in any way seem to be related to, or a replacement for, an out of gas message.  Indeed, that wouldn't make sense; if the transaction ran out of gas, its events would be reverted, and so there would be no events (ambiguous or otherwise) to show.  I think the fact that you're seeing \"ambiguous events\" messages is simply unrelated.\r\n\r\nI can look into the ambiguous events messages (because some of the ones I am seeing are... not really ambiguous?) but depending on exactly what's going on there it may be a while before it's fixed.  I would be helpful to know exactly how these ambiguous events messages differed from your expectations and what you considered to be wrong with them!\r\n\r\n@SidSethi I think you can leave this open, I think we've agreed to use this one for what I called the first issue?  But yeah filing issues for the others would be good.",
